# Widget Development

## Overview

The widget is a standalone JavaScript file that can be embedded on any website. It's built with vanilla TypeScript and has no external dependencies.

## Location

```
widget/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts       # Entry point
│   ├── capture.ts     # Screenshot/recording
│   ├── annotate.ts    # Annotation tools
│   ├── ui.ts          # Widget UI
│   └── submit.ts      # Submission + offline queue
├── dist/
│   └── feedbackflow.js  # Built widget script
├── build.mjs          # Build script (esbuild)
└── tsconfig.json
```

## Building

```bash
npm run widget:build    # Build widget script
npm run widget:dev      # Watch mode
npm run widget:typecheck # TypeScript check
```

Output: `widget/dist/feedbackflow.js` (target: <50KB minified)

## Embedding

```html
<script
  src="https://cdn.feedbackflow.dev/widget.js"
  data-widget-key="wk_xxxxx"
  data-position="bottom-right"
></script>
```

## Widget Features

- **Screenshot capture** - html2canvas or native API
- **Screen recording with audio** - getDisplayMedia + MediaRecorder
- **Annotation tools** - Pen (red), highlighter (yellow), shapes (circle, arrow)
- **Offline queue** - localStorage with retry
- **Configurable styling** - Position, colors, button text

## Widget Config Options

```typescript
interface WidgetConfig {
  position: "bottom-right" | "bottom-left" | "top-right" | "top-left";
  buttonText?: string;
  primaryColor?: string;
  backgroundColor?: string;
  textColor?: string;
  logoUrl?: string;
}
```

## Submission Flow

1. User clicks widget button
2. Modal opens with capture options
3. User captures screenshot or records screen
4. Optional: annotate screenshot
5. Fill form (title, description, type, email)
6. Submit to `/api/widget/submit`
7. On failure: queue in localStorage, retry later

## API Endpoint

```typescript
// POST /api/widget/submit
{
  widgetKey: string;
  type: "bug" | "feature";
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  screenshotBase64?: string;
  recordingBlob?: Blob;
  submitterEmail?: string;
  submitterName?: string;
  metadata: {
    browser: string;
    os: string;
    url: string;
    screenWidth: number;
    screenHeight: number;
    userAgent: string;
    timestamp: number;
  };
}
```

## Rate Limiting

- 10 submissions per minute per IP
- 100 submissions per day per widget
- Honeypot field for spam detection

## Development Rules

1. **No external dependencies** - Keep bundle small
2. **Works across browsers** - Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
3. **No AI client-side** - All AI processing happens server-side
4. **Graceful degradation** - Handle permission denials
5. **Recording limit** - 2 minutes max
